{
  "text": "This disorder was described by Crohn in 1932 after studying 14 cases of TI. CD patterns involve transmural inflammation, thickened submucosa, fissuring ulceration and non-caseating granulomas. It is frequently followed by a number of symptoms such as abdominal pain, diarrhea, gastrointestinal bleeding, malabsorption, and weight loss, and may lead to lifethreatening complications [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
